schema.title: DocumentEnvelope
schema.description: Data model to convey any kind of document, any format with associated meta data to help the identification and the decoding.

payload.description: This contains the payload of the document. It can either be raw data or encoded data in b6se4. see details in metaData block.

metaData.title: DocumentEnvelope_MetaData
metaData.description: Meta data associated to payload inside document envelope, helping to read/understand the DocumentEnvelope payload.

documentType.description: Type of the document in the payload defined by the "grammarOwner"

name.description: Document name: name of the document in the payload (namespace, see domain)

creationDateTime.description: Date of the trip point optional time and time offset in ISO 8601 format, e.g. 2017-02-10T20:40:00+02:00

bookingNumber.description: Ticket No(Specially for Air and Train segment)

start.title: start
start.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

localDateTime.description: Local Date/Time of the itinerary end in format ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS)

name.description: Label associated to the location (e.g. Eiffel Tower, Madison Square)

lines.description: Line 1 = Street address, Line 2 = Apartment, suite, unit, building, floor, etc

stateCode.description: State code (two character standard IATA state code)

text.description: Field containing a full unformatted address. Only applicable when the fields lines, postalCode, countryCode, cityName are not filled.

end.title: end
end.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

localDateTime.description: Local Date/Time of the itinerary end in format ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS)

name.description: Label associated to the location (e.g. Eiffel Tower, Madison Square)

travelAgency.title: travelAgency
travelAgency.description: details on the travel agency owning the trip

officeName.description: Office name of the travel agency

countryCode.description: Country code of the country (ISO3166-1). E.g. "US" for the United States

number.description: Phone number. Composed of digits only. The number of digits depends on the country.

name.title: name
name.description: Description of the name of a physical person

title.description: Contains all the suffixes and prefixes that can be appended to a name - Mr, Miss, Pr. - E.g. " Mr".

middleName.description: Middle name(s), for example "Lee" in "John Lee Smith".

currency.description: currency Code apply to all elements of the price

checkInDate.description: heck-in date of the stay (hotel local date). Format YYYY-MM-DD The lowest accepted value is today date (no dates in the past).

checkOutDate.description: check-out date of the stay (hotel local date). Format YYYY-MM-DD The lowest accepted value is checkInDate+1.

serviceProviderName.description: car provider information(Car rental compay name)

stakeholder.title: stakeholder
stakeholder.description: Definition of PNR travelers. Fields gender, nationality, placeOfBirth, countryOfResidence are only populated for passengerDelivery resources.

passangerTypeCode.description: 3-characters code defining the passenger type - possible values: ADT, CHD, INS, INF, UNA

departure.title: departure
departure.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

subType.description: Location sub-type (e.g. airport, port, rail-station, restaurant, atm...)

name.description: Label associated to the location (e.g. Eiffel Tower, Madison Square)

arrival.title: arrival
arrival.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

subtype.description: Location sub-type (e.g. airport, port, rail-station, restaurant, atm...)

name.description: Label associated to the location (e.g. Eiffel Tower, Madison Square)

number.description: Seat number corresponding to the concatenation of the seatmap row and the column information, for example 12B'

cabin.description: Cabin code associated to the seat

vehicle.title: vehicle
vehicle.description: Vehicle describes the transportation means e.g. a Train, a Bus, etc. It may be further characterized, in the case of a Train, it contains the Train Number, Code etc.

vehicleType.description: Code (codelist TVT) for the generic transport service returned, e.g. High speed, Intercities, Night and so on

associatedEquipments.title: associatedEquipments
associatedEquipments.description: Used to convey information about special equipments (GPS, Baby seat, ...) associated to the car booking.

pickup.title: pickup
pickup.description: Pick-up location and time of the rented vehicle.

localDateTime.description: local date and time compliant with ISO8601.

location.title: location
location.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

dropoff.title: dropoff
dropoff.description: dropoff location and time of the rented vehicle.

localDateTime.description: local date and time compliant with ISO8601.

acrissCode.description: Association of car rental industry systems standards

description.title: description
description.description: Specific type to convey a list of string for specific information type ( via qualifier) in specific character set, or language

adults.description: number of adult guests (1-9) per room

childAge.description: Comma separated list of ages of each child at the time of check-out from the hotel. If several children have the same age, the ages will be repeated.

type.description: Room type code, 3 character identifier of the room. The first character identifies the room type category. The second numeric character identifies the number of beds. The third character identifies the bed type. There is a special case where ROH is returned, this value stands for Run Of House.

typeEstimated.title: typeEstimated
typeEstimated.description: estimated room category, bed type and number of beds in the room. This information has been parsed from the room description, and is thus only provided for informational purposes

beds.description: Number of beds in the room (1-9)

weight.title: weight
weight.description: An object representing weight and unit.

amount.description: Defines the weight value with the specified unit with decimal position.

code.description: Code of the meal served on board

description.description: Description of the meal served on board

departureAirportLocation.title: departureAirportLocation
departureAirportLocation.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

name.description: Label associated to the location (e.g. Eiffel Tower, Madison Square)

arrivalAirportLocation.title: arrivalAirportLocation
arrivalAirportLocation.description: Description of a particular point or place in physical space

name.description: Label associated to the location (e.g. Eiffel Tower, Madison Square)

localDateTime.description: Local schedule dateTime of the departure or arrival. Conversion of dateTime in local date time.
Local schedule dateTime of the departure or arrival. Conversion of dateTime in local date time.

aircraftDescription.description: aircraft description (ex BOEING 737 ALL SERIES PASSENGER)

carrier.title: carrier
carrier.description: Includes the common name of the carrier (Operating or Marketing)

carrierCode.description: Two letter IATA standard carrier code

code.description: A machine-readable warning code from the Canned Messages table, that will enable the API Consumers code to handle this type of warning

title.description: An warning title from the Canned Messages table with a 1:1 correspondence to the error code. This may be localized

detail.description: An easy-to-read explanation specific to this occurrence of the problem. It should give the API consumer an idea of what went wrong and how to recover from it. Like the title, this field’s value can be localized.

parameter.description: The key of the URI path or query parameter that caused the warning

pointer.description: A JSON Pointer RFC6901 to the associated entity in the request body that caused this warning

example.description: A sample input to guide the user when resolving this issue

status.description: The HTTP status code of this response. This is present only in terminal errors which cause an unsuccessful response. In the case of multiple errors, they must all have the same status.
